http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: This course offers the serious horticulture student an in depth study of greenhouse management practices. Structural considerations are covered, as well as plant propagation techniques, pesticide use, and marketing strategies. The student will receive ample opportunity to practice the skills learned during the course.
